Introduction¶

This project analyzes the $CO_2$ emissions (tonnes per person) dataset taken from Gapminder.

The dataset contains yearly $CO_2$ emissions from the burning of fossil fuels (metric tonnes of $CO_2$ per person).

In [29]:
# percentage of CO2 emission in 2014
emission_2014 = df.iloc[-1].sort_values(ascending=False)
percent = emission_2014/sum(emission_2014)*100
In [30]:
# group CO2 emissions less than 1% into 'rest' category
percent_threshold = percent[percent > 0.7]
percent_threshold['rest'] = percent[percent <= 0.7].sum()
In [31]:
percent_threshold.plot(kind='pie', figsize=(16, 16), autopct='%1.0f%%', title='CO2 emission in 2014')
Out[31]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x7f9c3c2e17d0>

Conclusion:

Countries having maximum per capita $CO_2$ emission in 2014: Qatar, Trinidad and Tobago, Kuwait
Countries having minimum per capita $CO_2$ emission in 2014: Burundi, Somalia, Chad

def color_negative_red(val):
    """
    Takes a scalar and returns a string with
    the css property `'color: green'` for negative
    strings, red otherwise.
    """
    color = 'green' if val < 0 else 'red'
    return 'background-color: %s' % color
